						<p>On the West and South walls of the central shrine, Nāgēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 5: 976 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records a gift of 97 sheep for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Tirukkīḻkōṭṭattu-Mahādēva by a shepherd named Dēvaṉ Nakkaṉ.</p>						

